5|$|He {{has also}} collaborated with Pierre Christin {{on a number}} of non-Valérian projects. The first of these was Lady Polaris in 1987, an {{illustrated}} novel about the mysterious disappearance of a cargo vessel, the Lady Polaris. The narrative comprises various documents related to the lost ship: comic strips, log books, even an <b>investigative</b> <b>journalism</b> account by a fictionalised Mézières and Christin. The action takes place against the backdrop of many of the great seaports of Europe. Mézières undertook considerable research in putting together this book, visiting the ports of Liverpool, Copenhagen, Antwerp, Rotterdam, Hamburg, Lübeck, Bordeaux, Bilbao and Genoa.|$|E
